stylometry: Decision trees are important because it allows the problem to be laid out in front of you and your able to see all the different outcomes possible, if either a possitive, negative or neutral solution.  They solve for the EMV, which normal spreadsheets cannot do.  In solving for EMV, it makes it easier to solve for the EVSI and EVPI. An example is if a company want to mine for gold in a mountain, you take in factors such as mining cost, possible profit, hiring a specialist to determine if mining is a good idea, probability of a positive or negative outcome, probability of a positive or negative outcome if the specialist gives a favorable or unfavorable recommendation.  The tree the allow you to branch off into different scenarios or decisions and shows you the outcome and profit or loss of each decision and its outcome.
